i got stuck with no way to proceeed, I saw port 2049 is vulnerable, but couldnt mount it. I looked up help and found the command
showmount -e <ADDRESS> 
This gives us the share TechSupport
Port 2049 is an NFS share
so create a mount folder like so: mkdir ~/mnt
then:
sudo mount -t nfs 10.129.202.41:/TechSupport <MOUNTFOLDER> -o nolock

Then sudo su, as you are not permitted on default account to open this share, there are a bunch of text files
root: cd ~/mnt/
cat *    -> reads all the text files
In here are credentials for a user called alex.
These credentials can be used to log in via xfreerdp
Inside /users/alex/ is a text file called IMPORTANT
this has sa:PASSWORD
Trying to access users/Administrator on this share with that password, works, which confirms this password is for Administrator on the server

again start a new rdp session but using the Administrator and the password for it we found in IMPORTANT.txt

